createVestedERC20(bytes32,bytes32,uint8,.details: Uses a modified minimal proxy contract that stores immutable parameters in code and passes them in through calldata. See ClonesWithCallData.

params.decimals: The number of decimals used by the VestedERC20 token
params.endTimestamp: The end time of the vest, must be greater than startTimestamp, Unix timestamp in seconds
params.name: The name of the VestedERC20 token
params.startTimestamp: The start time of the vest, Unix timestamp in seconds
params.symbol: The symbol of the VestedERC20 token
params.underlying: The ERC20 token that is vested

implementation().notice: The VestedERC20 used as the template for all clones created

userdoc.notice: Factory for deploying VestedERC20 contracts cheaply
